 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Against MWHYL:<br />
Set up fast - usually the drain of three will hurt them fast.  with a presence on most of the sites the loss of the bonus will not be too great. Make visage count. Set for Stun the apprentice.  This is one of the better match ups. I can hold off against surprise assualt with good power and enclosed vehicles. For spies i have Snipers.<br />
<br />
Hidden Base<br />
X-swarm: be very careful in space. start security percautions and don't go up until they filp. again make sure visage and the ground drain eat away.<br />
<br />
Numbers: Should throw in tortures - don't quite know where yet. need some more help here.<br />
<br />
Mains:<br />
I can mount a pretty strong ground force. Have moved BFHI in and out to slow them down, toyed with ghhhhk. This decks speed has made the difference in the games.<br />
<br />
I think this is good deck.  It seems to lack the 'expert' care to make it great. But the concept is very solid.  Any ideas positive or negative will be appreciated.	</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
